# CCCAGG Pairs Absent

**Endpoint**: `/data/cccagg/pairs/absent`  
**Category**: GeneralInfo  
**Documentation**: [https://developers.coindesk.com/documentation/legacy/Other/cccaggPairsAndExchangesAbsentEndpoint](https://developers.coindesk.com/documentation/legacy/Other/cccaggPairsAndExchangesAbsentEndpoint)

## Description

Pairs absent from CCCAGG

## Parameters

No parameters required.

## Test Results

**Total Tests**: 1  
**Successful**: 1  
**Failed**: 0  
**Success Rate**: 100.0%

## Example Usage

### cURL

```bash
curl -X GET "https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/data/cccagg/pairs/absent"
```

### Python

```python
import requests

# Endpoint: /data/cccagg/pairs/absent
url = "https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/data/cccagg/pairs/absent"

response = requests.get(url)

if response.status_code == 200:
    data = response.json()
    print(data)
else:
    print(f"Error: {response.status_code}")
```

### JavaScript

```javascript
// Endpoint: /data/cccagg/pairs/absent
const url = "https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/data/cccagg/pairs/absent";

fetch(url)
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => console.log(data))
  .catch(error => console.error('Error:', error));
```
